s with every possible intrinsic detail with an aim to automate the flow of information &amp; conventional processes.<\/em>&nbsp;&#8211; <strong>Mr. Vikas Mishra &#8211; Executive Director, Gozoom Technologies&nbsp;<\/strong><\/b><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are many different ways to track warehouse inventory. Some go paper-based, others go electronic\u2014some track inventory in real-time, others in the batch.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For warehouse inventory management to work, you must have proper inventory levels. Without that, you can&#8217;t know whether your inventory is running low, whether you have enough on hand to meet demand, and get the best possible price when you sell your products.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ah! It is a grim story because there is no handbook for managing your inventory accurately.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yes, there are tips and tricks Google is flooded with, and particular textual material as well.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Still, this cannot give one perfect solution to handle your inventory without any flaws.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Many businesses lose thousands of dollars due to a lack of inventory management because they don&#8217;t take one essential step, such as creating a system to manage their warehouse inventory.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ouch! It hurts!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No need to be so melodramatic! Digitalization has handled the situation very well.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"blog-video-center\" title=\"Gozoom Technologies:Warehouse management system\" src=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/web-stories\/benefits-of-warehouse-management-system\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Welcome_to_the_Warehouse_Inventory_Management_Solution\"><\/span><b>Welcome to the Warehouse Inventory Management Solution!<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Warehouse inventory management is the process by which stock stored in a warehouse or other storage facility is received, tracked, audited, and managed for order fulfillment.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A warehouse manager is responsible for maintaining inventory levels, ensuring that the right of way is clear, and ensuring that all activities \u2014 receiving, storing, moving, processing, and delivering \u2014 are conducted safely and organized.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Three_Major_Warehouse_Inventory_Management_Techniques\"><\/span><b>Three Major Warehouse Inventory Management Techniques<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Push system for inventory management<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pull system for managing inventory<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Just-in-time inventory management system<\/span>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"hbblog-cta\" style=\"background: #fdfdfd!important; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 35px 25px 35px 25px; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #dfdfdf; border-radius: 5px; border-bottom-color: #f5bd00; border-bottom-width: 3px!important;\">\n<div class=\"hbblog-cta\">\n<h6 style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 24px!important; color: #212121; font-family: 'Open Sans',sans-serif; line-height: 36px;\">Get Developed Your Own Warehouse Inventory Management Solution<\/h6>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"hbblog-cta-btn\" style=\"margin-top: 20px!important;\"><a style=\"background: #282f6f; color: #fff; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 20px; border-radius: 3px;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/inquiry.html\">Inquire Now<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Warehouse_Inventory_Management_Methodologies\"><\/span><b>Warehouse Inventory Management Methodologies<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Just-in-time\"><\/span><b><i>Just-in-time<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">JIT, sometimes referred to as just-in-time or JIT delivery, is a delivery method for small batches of products that are produced at the last minute and shipped quickly. It is often used to manufacture products that need to be high-quality and fresh, such as food products, medical goods, and pharmaceuticals.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Cross-Docking\"><\/span><b><i>Cross-Docking<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cross-docking is an efficient inventory management strategy and helps to receive and load docks facing each other with goods transferred across from one to another. In cross-docking, the receiving dock is loaded while the sending dock is unloading. This allows cross-docking to be as efficient as possible. Because of cross-docking, the docks never need to be loaded from both ends simultaneously.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"ABC_Analysis\"><\/span><b><i>ABC Analysis<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A business most commonly performs ABC analyses. They are important tools for managing your inventory and allocating the appropriate resources to your inventory management strategy. In ABC analysis, you classify your items into three categories: A for best sellers (usually 20% of your inventory), B for your medium sellers (usually 30%), and C for your lowest sellers (usually 50% of inventory).<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Two-bin_Method\"><\/span><b><i>Two-bin Method<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this two-bin system, you would put the working stock of the item in the working bin in the reserve bin when storage is nearing capacity to have more working stock on hand at any time. The other method, called the single-bin method, involves storing your working stock of an item in one bin and your reserve stock in another.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Fixed_Order_Quantity\"><\/span><b><i>Fixed Order Quantity<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With fixed-order quantity, you can order exactly what you need when you need it, without the stock sitting on the shelf. By reducing wasted inventory, you can meet the demands of high-volume customers more quickly and reduce the need for daily restocking.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Fixed-Period_Ordering\"><\/span><b>Fixed-Period Ordering<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also known as FPO or simply the FPO method, this technique ensures the same quantity is always placed on the same day.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite the repetition, the fixed-period order remains a viable form of ordering. It is common to repurpose these orders for other purposes, such as managing volatility or calculating the cost of a trade.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The fixed-period order is a trade form closely tied with inventory control and, ultimately, stock-keeping, which are fundamental business processes. By understanding this technique, an asset manager learns how to manage inventories and reduce the risk of fast-selling items sitting on the shelf. It can also eliminate the need to purchase back inventory and better match supply and demand.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Vendor-Managed_Inventory\"><\/span><b><i>Vendor-Managed Inventory<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vendor-managed inventory techniques are a relatively new strategy for fulfilling a product or service demand. Companies use this strategy when they expect to sell a product or service in large volumes relatively quickly. Vendor-managed inventory techniques rely on a vendor contacting a supplier when a purchase needs to be made and coordinating the purchase and shipment of the product.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Drop-Shipping\"><\/span><b><i>Drop-Shipping<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Drop Shipping method eliminates the need to hold inventory. When a customer orders an item, you purchase it from a supplier and ship it directly to the customer. The supplier ships the item directly to the customer. You then re-package and ship the item to the customer.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Warehouse_Inventory_Management_Challenges\"><\/span><b>Warehouse Inventory Management Challenges<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Complexity in supplying products quickly<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keeping track of the needs of your customers<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Achieving accuracy in inventory counts<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Determining how much inventory is <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">just right<\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is complicated.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Best_practices_to_build_an_efficient_warehouse_management_solution\"><\/span><b>Best practices to build an efficient warehouse management solution<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Prioritize_Your_Inventory\"><\/span><b><i>Prioritize Your Inventory<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first step in managing your inventory is to establish what inventory items are integral to the successful operation of your business and which are causing it to lose money or otherwise underperform.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Beginning with what you already have and then adding new <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">inventory can be the first step in turning a losing inventory situation into a <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">winning one.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Track_Product_Information\"><\/span><b><i>Track Product Information<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you begin to understand your inventory&#8217;s value, you&#8217;ll be able to determine where improvements can be made and take action to achieve them.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep detailed records of all inventory items at any given moment &#8211; this is critical to managing your inventory effectively. You will be surprised at how much this will affect your business&#8217;s bottom line.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Regular_Inventory_Audit\"><\/span><b><i>Regular Inventory Audit&nbsp;<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An audit can uncover hidden costs, reduce waste, improve inventory management and help you save money. When you regularly audit your inventory, you can determine what types of inventory items you should be keeping for your company so you can meet your needs and your goals as a business.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Track_Sales\"><\/span><b><i>Track Sales<\/i><\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tracking sales is another seemingly obvious trick that can help manage inventory. Tracking sales is not just about setting goals and keeping tabs on the percentage reached. It is also about identifying trends, seeing where there is an area of weakness, and planning a strategy to correct that area. It is about noticing when a new market opportunity emerges and learning when to commit and on what terms.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_Are_the_Benefits_of_a_WMS\"><\/span><b>What Are the Benefits of a WMS?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Faster Inventory Turnover<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Enhanced Customer and Supplier Relationships<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Warehouse Personnel Reduced<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Better Stock Control<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Optimised Warehouse Space<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Improved Labour Productivity<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reduce Operating Expenses<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Strengthen Security<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Optimize Inbound and Outbound Logistics<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Enhance Billing Management<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What%E2%80%99s_the_final_take\"><\/span><b>What&#8217;s the final take?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The ways in which we store, move, and display our inventory are evolving to make our operations more efficient. Today&#8217;s warehousing environment requires more than a peek at inventory to help you navigate your storage and movement needs. Intelligent, granular visibility into inventory is critical to making the most out of the space you have and, at the same time, keeping costs under control.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A WMS with the right set of capabilities can help you maximize the value of your inventory and lower costs.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span><b>Conclusion<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&#8217;re ready to build a WMS, make sure that the company you are considering has the right capabilities for your needs &#8211; one size definitely does <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">not<\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> fit all where a WMS is concerned.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Gozoom Technologies, we have built the right solution for multiple warehouses with the innovation, functionality, and versatility they need to grow and thrive.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><b>As we know, a good software solution will not only help you get more done but will also teach you how to be more efficient, too.<\/b><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have the required skills and expertise to build customizable warehouse software solutions to help you track your inventory, print labels, and seamlessly operate across different channels.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style